1 SECTION 5. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6-130.1 of Title 37A, unless
3 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. An establishment licensed by the Alcoholic Beverage Laws
5 Enforcement (ABLE) Commission that claims that the actions of an
6 employee are not attributable to the establishment licensed by the
7 ABLE Commission under this act, shall provide to the ABLE
8 Commission, not later than ten (10) days after receipt of an
9 administrative notice of violation, an affidavit indicating that the
10 establishment licensed by the ABLE Commission was in compliance with
11 the requirements of this act at the time of the violation for which
12 the administrative notice was issued. At a hearing in which the
13 establishment licensed by the ABLE Commission claims the benefits of
14 this act, the establishment licensed by the ABLE Commission may be
15 required to present additional evidence to support such claim.
16 B. At a time when an employee does not possess a currently
17 valid employee license from the ABLE Commission, the action of the
18 employee shall be attributable to the establishment licensed by the
19 ABLE Commission if the employee:
20 1. Sells, furnishes, or gives an alcoholic beverage to:
21 a. a person who is insane or mentally deficient,
22 b. a minor, or
23 c. an intoxicated person; or
24 2. Allows consumption of an alcoholic beverage by:
